  "page_type": "function",
  "name": "OnIpReceivePrepare",
  "category": "TCPIPAPI",
  "title": "OnIpReceivePrepare",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/TCPIPAPI/EventProcedures/CAPLfunctionTCPIPOnIpReceivePrepare.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "long OnIpReceivePrepare(ethernetPacket * packet);"
  ],
  "description": [
    "If the CAPL program implements this callback it is called right before a received packet will be dispatched to the TCP/IP stack.",
    "It is possible to manipulate the content of the packet or to block the receiving of the package from the bus."
  ],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "packet",
      "type": "",
      "description": "The received Ethernet packet."
    }
  ],
  "return": "",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "long OnIpReceivePrepare(ethernetPacket * packet)\n{\n  // block all packets with a broadcast destination MAC id\n  if(packet.destination == 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFLL)\n  {\n    write(\"packet blocked\");\n    return 0;\n  }\n  write(\"packet passed to tcp/ip stack\");\n  return 1;\n}"
  },
